OL,3,CMet Office issues ice warning as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to drop
OL,6,FForecasters are warning that a
OL,7,Fcombination of wet surfaces from
OL,8,Frecent rainfall and a dip in
OL,9,Ftemperatures will create hazardous
OL,10,Fconditions.
OL,12,FAccording to the Met Office,
OL,13,Ftemperatures are expected to fall
OL,14,Fclose to or even below freezing
OL,15,Fovernight. This drop is likely to
OL,16,Fcause icy patches to form on untreated
OL,17,Fsurfaces, including roads, pavements,
OL,18,Fand cycle paths.
